cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with object discovery in 3D point clouds using a convolutional neural network. The most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the paper deals with image processing and object recognition. The second likely category is cs.RO (Robotics) as the paper deals with sensors like Microsoft Kinect and the discovery of objects in 3D space. The third likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper uses a Siamese network and non-linear embedding to train the model. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper deals with the discovery of never-seen-before objects. The fifth likely category is cs.GR (Graphics) as the paper deals with point cloud data and clustering in the learned embedding space of supervoxels.
